The White House Press Secretary released a statement on World Humanitarian Day, acknowledging the dedication and bravery of humanitarian workers who risk their lives to provide assistance to those affected by conflict and violence. The statement highlights the efforts of aid workers in providing food, medicine, and shelter to refugees and internally displaced persons in Syria, as well as their role in helping communities become more resilient in crisis-prone areas. The United States expresses solidarity with humanitarian workers and calls on all countries to ensure their safety and support their efforts in building a more secure and prosperous world.